A list of standard orders, facilities, and related activities, in the video game Death Stranding by Kojima Productions. Read more ‚Ä£

Notes
Table Columns
Order Completion
If your browsers local storage API is available, you can keep track of completed orders.
Order Number
The Standard Order number.
Objectives
This includes both regular & premium deliveries, marked in parenthesis. If one will grant Materials to a destination, look for the Material designation in the Objectives tab.
Category
This is the primary order evaluation category that will receive the most Likes to.
Likes
The maximum number of likes for a regular and premium delivery.
Weight
The total weight of the delivery.
Size
The amount of cargo and size of cargo. i.e. M-10 = Medium x10. This is to assist with maximum cargo that can be load on Sam's back, or in a truck.
Types of Orders
Orders for Sam
Primary missions that advance the story.
Standard Orders
Optional secondary missions that earns you more Likes and Stars and provide access to more materials.
Premium Deliveries
Optional stricter requirements on Standard Orders‚Äîsuch as less damage or a shorter time limit‚Äîthat earns you more Likes.
Order Evaluation Categories
Bridge Link
Represents ycategory-our connections to other players, characters, and BB.
Cargo Condition
Orders that category-must be delivered with minimal damage.
Delivery Time
Orders that category-must be delivered within a specified time limit.
Delivery Volume
Orders in whcategory-ich a bulk items must be delivered.
Miscellaneous
Orders that forge new delivery routes, involve traveling into BT-heavy areas, clearing out MULE camps, and delivering lost cargo.
Appendix
Cargo Collection
Pick up the cargo from the collection point.
Cargo Collection from a BT Area
Watch out for BTs. They have been known to appear in the area from which the cargo must be collected.
Cargo Collection from the Vog
Watch out for the toxic gas known as "vog" in the area from which the cargo must be collected.
Cargo Recovery from a MULE Camp
Watch out for MULEs. The cargo must be recovered from one of their camps.
Cargo Recovery from Terrorists
Watch out for terrorists in the area from which the cargo must be recovered.
Cargo Sizes
Cargo comes in four sizes, corresponding to weight: small (S), medium (M), large (L), and extra large (XL).
Chilled Delivery
1. "Chilled delivery" cargo will slowly deteriorate in warm areas. To keep such cargo in good condition, try to remain in sheltered areas and avoid direct sunlight. Exposing the cargo to rain and snow also helps to keep it cool.
2. High atmospheric temperatures and thermal pads will damage this cargo.
Chiral Waste
Cargo that has been contaminated by chiralium, and subsequently abandoned. Should be disposed at the bottom of a crater lake.
Delivery to Mountainous Area
This is a difficult delivery in a mountainous area. Watch out for slopes and inclines.
Delivery to Remote Area
Watch your footing. The cargo needs to be delivered to a remote and inhospitable area.
Delivery to Snowy Mountain Area
This is a difficult delivery to a snowy, mountainous area. Be sure to take precautions against the cold weather.
Do Not Submerge
Do not submerge this cargo in rivers or other bodies of water. Water can enter the container and cause damage to its contents. Be especially careful when crossing rivers and streams.
Fragile Cargo
1. This cargo has low durability, and can be destroyed very easily. Try to avoid vibration and impact.
2. Cargo must be carried in the hands at all times. Contents are extremely delicate. Even minor jolts and vibrations can cause damage.
Re-Orders
Certain Standard Orders will only become available to let you "replay" some of Sam's Orders after you have beaten the game.
Undefined (ÔøΩ)
This symbol indicates that a value is missing or broken.
Urgent
Certain Standard Orders are marked as "urgent" which are often time-sensitive.
